        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thy abode - Margin, 'Sitting.' Among the Hebrews, sitting down, rising up, and going out, were phrases to describe the whole of a man's life and actions (compare Deuteronomy 6:7; Deuteronomy 28:6; 1 Kings 3:7; Psalm 121:8). God here says that he knew the place where he dwelt, and he was able to return him again to it Isaiah 37:29.",
        "children": [
